headline: Is Chipotle Fairly Priced After Its Sharp 2025 Share Price Rebound?
summary: Wondering if Chipotle Mexican Grill is finally looking tasty again after its brutal sell off, or if the market still has indigestion? You are not alone. The stock has bounced recently, up about 7.5% over the last week and 14.5% over the past month, even though it is still down roughly 39.7% year to date and 44.2% over the last year. This is a classic setup that can signal either a recovery in confidence or a value trap. Part of the renewed interest has come as investors refocus on Chipotle's...
